Obama hosted the inaugural summit of the Obama Foundation in Chicago from October 31 to November 1, 2017.[512] Obama intends for the foundation to be the central focus of his post-presidency and part of his ambitions for his subsequent activities following his presidency to be more consequential than his time in office.[513] Obama has also written a presidential memoir, in a reported $65Â million deal with Penguin Random House.[514] The book, A Promised Land, was released on November 17, 2020.[515][516][517]
